ENTRY       EC 2.8.2.32                 Enzyme
NAME        scymnol sulfotransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring sulfur-containing groups;
            Sulfotransferases
SYSNAME     3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate:5beta-scymnol sulfotransferase
REACTION    3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + 5beta-scymnol = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + 5beta-scymnol sulfate [RN:R07798]
ALL_REAC    R07798
SUBSTRATE   3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate [CPD:C00053];
            5beta-scymnol [CPD:C16260]
PRODUCT     adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate [CPD:C00054];
            5beta-scymnol sulfate [CPD:C16261]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the shark Heterodontus portusjacksoni is able to sulfate the C27 bile salts 5beta-scymnol (the natural bile salt) and 5alpha-cyprinol (the carp bile salt). Enzyme activity is activated by Mg2+ but inhibited by the product 5beta-scymnol sulfate.
